data: {"type":"response.output_text.done","sequence_number":378,"item_id":"msg_05c456d2351c9d3700693b2e37e5248195afaf4d526c7a32a5","output_index":4,"content_index":0,"text":"I’m not sure which “secondary agent” you mean — could you tell me the context (software product, multi‑agent system, call center, robotics, security, etc.)? Meanwhile, here are common roles and capabilities a secondary agent typically performs:\n\nGeneral capabilities\n- Backup / failover: take over if the primary fails to keep services running.\n- Monitoring & alerting: watch system health and notify humans or trigger remediation.\n- Delegated tasks: handle lower‑priority or specialized subtasks the primary offloads.\n- Data collection & logging: gather telemetry, audit trails, or usage stats.\n- Validation & safety checks: verify actions proposed by the primary (sanity checks, constraints).\n- Orchestration support: coordinate workers, queue jobs, or schedule tasks.\n- Rate limiting / throttling: enforce limits so the primary isn’t overloaded.\n- Retry & recovery: attempt retries, rollbacks, or cleanup after errors.\n- Security/enforcement: enforce policies, isolate suspicious activity, or run scans.\n- Decision support: provide recommendations, analytics, or alternative plans to the primary.\n\nExamples by domain\n- Customer support: a secondary chatbot that handles common FAQs and escalates complex issues to a human or the primary bot.\n- Robotics: a secondary controller that manages sensor fusion and safety interlocks while the primary focuses on high‑level planning.\n- Distributed systems / microservices: a sidecar agent that handles logging, metrics, and health checks for the main service.\n- Cybersecurity: a secondary agent that isolates compromised endpoints and performs forensics while the primary continues business functions.\n- DevOps: an agent that performs deployments and rollbacks under the orchestration of the primary CI/CD manager.\n\nIf you tell me the exact system or role, I’ll give precise capabilities, example workflows, and recommended implementation patterns.","logprobs":[]}

